This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents two algorithms for Bayesian optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as Bayesian optimization is a popular technique in AI research. Additionally, the paper discusses frequentist regret guarantees, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the numerical results presented in the paper suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
